Class CartesianProductInMapIterator<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.util.collect.EZIterator<java.util.Map<K,V>>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssignmentMapsIterator

    @Beta
public class CartesianProductInMapIterator<K,V>
extends EZIterator<java.util.Map<K,V>>
    A iterator over the Cartesian product of the ranges of a map of iterators, indexed by an arbitrary type K. The constructor takes a map of iterator makers because each dimension but the first one will need to be iterated multiple times, so a new iterator will be needed for each sweeping. An iterator maker for a given key is required to make iterators over the same range every time.

    braz
